<Link id="l00043" /><CodeLine lineNumber="43"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// be filled in if the FunctionInfo contains a line table. If an address is</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00044" /><CodeLine lineNumber="44"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// for a concrete function with no inlined functions, this array will have</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00047" /><CodeLine lineNumber="47"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// the concrete function itself. This allows one address to generate</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00053" /><CodeLine lineNumber="53"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Function name regex patterns associated with a call site at the lookup</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00054" /><CodeLine lineNumber="54"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// address. This vector will be populated when:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00055" /><CodeLine lineNumber="55"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// 1 The lookup address matches a call site&#39;s return address in a function</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00056" /><CodeLine lineNumber="56"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// 2 The call site has associated regex patterns that describe what</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00057" /><CodeLine lineNumber="57"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// functions can be called from that location</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00058" /><CodeLine lineNumber="58"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00059" /><CodeLine lineNumber="59"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// The regex patterns can be used to validate function calls during runtime</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00060" /><CodeLine lineNumber="60"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// checking or symbolication. For example:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00061" /><CodeLine lineNumber="61"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// - Patterns like &quot;^foo$&quot; indicate the call site can only call function</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00062" /><CodeLine lineNumber="62"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// &quot;foo&quot;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00063" /><CodeLine lineNumber="63"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// - Patterns like &quot;^std::&quot; indicate the call site can call any function in</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00064" /><CodeLine lineNumber="64"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   the std namespace</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00065" /><CodeLine lineNumber="65"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// - Multiple patterns allow matching against a set of allowed functions</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00066" /><CodeLine lineNumber="66"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00067" /><CodeLine lineNumber="67"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// The patterns are stored as string references into the GSYM string table.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00068" /><CodeLine lineNumber="68"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// This information is typically loaded from:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00069" /><CodeLine lineNumber="69"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// - DWARF debug info call site entries</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00070" /><CodeLine lineNumber="70"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// - External YAML files specifying call site patterns</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00071" /><CodeLine lineNumber="71"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// - Other debug info formats that encode call site constraints</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00072" /><CodeLine lineNumber="72"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00073" /><CodeLine lineNumber="73"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// The patterns will be empty if:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00074" /><CodeLine lineNumber="74"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// - The lookup address is not at the return address of a call site</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00075" /><CodeLine lineNumber="75"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// - The call site has no associated function name constraints</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00076" /><CodeLine lineNumber="76"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// - Call site info was not included when creating the GSYM file</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
